"script": "If you stepped into the wrong river in the Amazon, an electric eel could stop your heart. Its body is packed with thousands of cells stacked like tiny batteries, all wired together. When it senses prey, it fires them at once, blasting out a jolt of six hundred volts. And this current shoots through the water, locking up the muscles of nearby fish so they can't even twitch. Then the eel swallows them whole, completely paralyzed. It can even leap from the water to press its shock straight into a larger threat.",
